  <a href="#1" id="1">
   Four imprisoned African National Congress leaders, convicted in 1964 with Nelson Mandela, were allowed to visit their ANC colleague at his isolated prison house.
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   The four men, all held at Pollsmoor Prison in Cape Town, were taken to nearby Victor Verster Prison on 12/23/1988 and spent about six hours with Mandela.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   Mandela was moved to the suburban-style home on the prison grounds 12/07/1988 after recovering from tuberculosis at a private clinic in Cape Town.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   Mandela's wife, Winnie, said after visiting her husband last month that he is being held "practically in solitary confinement" at the house.
  </a>
